post_text:
Late registration for all students new to the DuBois Area School District or those changing elementary schools in the fall of 2020 will take place Wednesday, July 22nd at the DUBOIS AREA MIDDLE SCHOOL. Personnel will be available from 9:00 a.m. to noon and 1:00 p.m. to 3:00 p.m. to assist with the registration process. Pre-registration packets are available at school offices from 8:00am until 4:00pm Monday through Thursday. Parents and guardians are encouraged to retrieve a pre-registration packet in advance to expedite the registration process. All registering students must bring their birth certificate, immunization records and proof of residency. (Examples: deed, lease, current utility bill, current credit card bill, property tax bill, vehicle registration or DOT Identification Card.)

Children who will begin kindergarten this fall must be five (5) years of age by July 1, 2020. First grade registrants who have not been in kindergarten should be six (6) by July 1, 2020.

post_text:
National School Nurse Day, May 6, 2020, is a time to celebrate the specialty practice of school nursing. In 1972, the National Association of School Nurses (NASN) created National School Nurse Day to recognize school nurses and acknowledge their role in the educational setting. NASN applauds the contributions school nurses make every day to improve the health, safety, and academic success of all students.

The School Nurse Day theme this year – School Nurses: Supporting Students in Times of Crisis – reinforces the changing times of 2020. This year, more than ever, all members of our school communities, school nurses included, have been required to take on unprecedented roles and adapt quickly to changes in their jobs. It is reflective of the significant roles school nurses have in the health care of their school communities to help make a healthier place for children and families to learn and grow during this crisis.

Thank you School Nurses for all you do!!!

post_text:
The Pennsylvania Department of Education announced today that all schools in the commonwealth will remain closed through at least April 6 as a result of the COVID-19 response efforts. The closure order could be extended beyond April 6 if necessary to save lives and stop the spread of COVID-19.

The DuBois Area School District remains committed to developing an online learning platform to educate the students in our community.

Thank you to everyone that has completed the technology needs assessment survey to help us to develop our plan. Because the response of the survey generated a greater need than anticipated, we are actively working with multiple vendors in an attempt to acquire the required number of hot spots to provide internet capabilities in homes that do not presently have it. At this time, we are doing everything we can to acquire the necessary resources to launch a successful online learning program.

Thank you for your support and patience as we work collaboratively to develop a plan to provide continuity in educating our students.

DASD School Community,

Please share some love and appreciation to these exceptional servant leaders! These selfless individuals work diligently every day to provide a nutritious breakfast and lunch to the students in our district. Now, they embrace an even greater challenge with courage and compassion. Thank you, DASD Food Service Department! We could never do it without you! We are most grateful for your service and admire your dedication during these challenging times.
On behalf of our District, we applaud you!

Today, we fed 498 children. Rest assured that we are prepared to feed even more.

We have prepared “weekend bags” to ensure our children stay nourished over the weekend.

If you are in need or know someone that is in need, we are here for you.

Please continue to share this opportunity.
